The paper discusses the linguistic style and readability of scientific abstracts and their impact on the success and viral capability of a scientific article. This suggests that the paper could fall under several sub-categories, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
